Before diving into the best practices, please note that you may need to adapt the globs depending on your specific project structure.

---
name: discordjs-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for using Discord.js in bot development
globs: **/*.{ts,js}
---

- Use `Intents` correctly to subscribe to necessary events
- Implement proper error handling and logging
- Utilize `Collection` for efficient data management
- Leverage `Discord.js` sharding for large-scale bots

---
name: itty-router-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for routing with Itty Router in Cloudflare Workers
globs: **/*.{ts,js}
---

- Use route parameters for dynamic routing
- Implement proper error handling middleware
- Utilize `Router.handle` for consistent request handling
- Keep routes organized and modular

---
name: langchain-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for using LangChain in AI applications
globs: **/*.{ts,js}
---

- Use appropriate `LLM` models for your use case
- Implement proper prompt engineering techniques
- Utilize `Chains` for complex task orchestration
- Ensure proper error handling and retries for API calls

---
name: typescript-best-practices.mdc
description: TypeScript coding standards and type safety guidelines
globs: **/*.{ts}
---

- Use strict null checks
- Prefer interface over type when possible
- Use type guards and assertions for runtime type checking
- Implement proper type inference to reduce explicit type annotations

---
name: cloudflare-workers-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for developing with Cloudflare Workers
globs: **/*.{ts,js}
---

- Optimize cold start times by minimizing dependencies
- Use `kv` namespaces for efficient data storage
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Utilize `wrangler` for local development and testing